<task id="032" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P23.A3 — IChatClient cluster verification gate</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>0.5-1 hour</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-2-3, ichatclient, p23-a, bff-api, testing, verification-gate</tags>
    <parallel-group>23-A-gate</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Verification gate for tasks 030 and 031; must run AFTER both batches complete to confirm cluster-level zero-failure state and record ledger outcome</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Verify the IChatClient streaming cluster (~30-50 tests per design.md §3.4) is fully closed
    out by the combined work of tasks 030 + 031. This task is a gate: it runs ONLY after both
    batches complete and validates the cluster-level zero-failure state per FR-14.

    Run the full streaming cluster filter and verify zero failures:
    `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Streaming|FullyQualifiedName~ChatClient" -c Release`

    Document cluster outcome in `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/repair-ledger.md`
    with: total tests touched, total now Pass, escalations filed (if any from 030/031), per-file
    LOC delta summary.

    Per project CLAUDE.md NFR-02: this task does NOT modify any test files; it only verifies and
    records. If failures remain in the cluster, file an escalation per §4.8 documenting which
    tests remain Failed and the proposed remediation — do NOT mark the cluster closed until
    zero failures.

    Per §6.2, EVERY test in the cluster must end in `repaired`, `real-bug-pending-fix`,
    `flaky-quarantined`, OR be archived via `*.cs.archived-2026-MM-DD` rename. `Failed` is
    FORBIDDEN at project close.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior test orchestrator running cluster-level verification gates.</role>

  <goal>
    The IChatClient streaming cluster is verified zero-failure across the union of tasks 030 + 031.
    `ledgers/repair-ledger.md` records the cluster outcome (tests touched, Pass count, escalation
    count, total LOC change) as the canonical artifact for Phase 4 exit-ledger reconciliation
    (FR-27).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="ledger">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/repair-ledger.md</file>
    <file purpose="batch-1-output">(task 030 output: streaming batch 1 repaired)</file>
    <file purpose="batch-2-output">(task 031 output: streaming batch 2 repaired)</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="FR-14">All IChatClient streaming cluster tests must end in §6.2 final end-state (zero failures)</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">No production code changes</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">No file edits in this task beyond the ledger; verification-only</constraint>
    <constraint source="§4.3">No test left in `Failed` state at cluster close</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per design.md §3.4 the IChatClient streaming cluster contains ~30-50 tests. Tasks 030 + 031
      split the work across disjoint file sets. This gate confirms the union is zero-failure
      before declaring P23.A complete. Per FR-21 (cross-track regression check), any new failure
      in tests not currently being worked HALTS all tracks — this gate makes that explicit for
      the IChatClient cluster.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="030" status="not-started">Streaming batch 1 (Services/Ai/Chat/Streaming*)</dependency>
      <dependency task="031" status="not-started">Streaming batch 2 (Services/Ai/Capabilities/Streaming*)</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/repair-ledger.md</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Confirm tasks 030 and 031 are status=completed in `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`. If either is incomplete, HALT and report.</step>
    <step order="2">Run cluster filter: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Streaming|FullyQualifiedName~ChatClient" -c Release`. Capture TRX output.</step>
    <step order="3">Verify zero failures. If non-zero, identify each remaining failure and file an escalation per §4.8 OR document as `real-bug-pending-fix` / `flaky-quarantined` per §6.2.</step>
    <step order="4">Tally cluster metrics: total tests in cluster, Pass count, Skip count (+ reason), files repaired, files archived, escalations filed.</step>
    <step order="5">Append cluster section to `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/repair-ledger.md` with date, task IDs (030/031), cluster name, metrics.</step>
    <step order="6">Mark P23.A complete in `current-task.md`. Verify `git status` shows ledger update only — no production code changes.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">test (cluster filter verification)</tool>
    <tool name="git">status</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/repair-ledger.md (IChatClient cluster section appended)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/current-task.md (P23.A marked complete)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Streaming|FullyQualifiedName~ChatClient"` returns zero failures</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`ledgers/repair-ledger.md` contains a dated section for IChatClient cluster with tests-touched, Pass count, escalations filed</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No test in the cluster is in `Failed` state</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`git status` shows only ledger + current-task.md modifications; no production code changes</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
